24:48.476 --> 24:49.997
What are you doing out here?

24:50.077 --> 24:52.717
I'm on night watch.

24:53.914 --> 24:56.036
You're on the staff?

24:56.116 --> 24:57.805
Why were you in group with everybody else?

24:57.885 --> 25:00.408
Well, I was just there as an observer.

25:00.488 --> 25:02.900
I mean, I introduced myself,
but I guess you were out of it.

25:05.826 --> 25:07.601
I'm gonna have to report this, you know?

25:15.703 --> 25:17.758
Okay, that wasn't funny.

25:17.838 --> 25:21.529
- It was a little funny.
- Yeah, you're the next Moms Mabley.

25:21.609 --> 25:23.697
Who's that?

25:23.777 --> 25:26.367
Oh, she's an old black comedian.
She died in the '70s.

25:26.447 --> 25:31.005
Oh, yeah, that's me, old, black, and dead.

25:31.085 --> 25:32.940
Yeah, she got me through, like...

25:33.020 --> 25:35.476
like three months
at this shitty place in Utah.

25:35.556 --> 25:40.347
Her and, uh, George Carlin,
Lenny Bruce, Richard Pryor.

25:40.827 --> 25:42.016
Lord Buckley.

25:42.096 --> 25:44.385
What, you're some kind of comedy expert?

25:45.465 --> 25:47.521
No, I'm just more of a fan.

25:47.601 --> 25:50.624
But, uh, I did do some open mics.

25:50.704 --> 25:52.684
How'd that go?

25:53.807 --> 25:57.113
I'm on a porch in rehab playing to a crowd
of one, how do you think it went?

26:19.033 --> 26:21.655
- That was you.
- Hmm?

26:21.735 --> 26:23.724
The cloves,
I smoked one at the table earlier.

26:23.804 --> 26:27.127
It was... stuck in the mesh.

26:27.207 --> 26:29.517
I smoked it.

26:32.379 --> 26:33.824
Well, look...

26:36.317 --> 26:38.038
Here you go.

26:38.118 --> 26:40.975
Full one for the road.

26:41.055 --> 26:44.111
You sure? It's your last one.

26:44.191 --> 26:45.829
Yeah, I've got another pack.

26:47.394 --> 26:49.032
Thanks.

26:55.536 --> 26:58.176
I get anxious here, too.

27:00.441 --> 27:02.229
Sterile white walls.

27:02.309 --> 27:03.880
Yeah.

27:05.012 --> 27:07.401
There's nothing there.

27:07.481 --> 27:09.518
Nothing but you.

27:12.285 --> 27:15.342
Come on, everybody, let's go. Two vans...

27:15.422 --> 27:17.611
Whoa, what are you two doing out here?

27:17.691 --> 27:20.900
Just having a smoke before the meeting.

27:22.129 --> 27:24.166
Let's go.

27:30.604 --> 27:33.642
Charlie, you coming?

27:35.109 --> 27:36.349
Yeah.

27:37.611 --> 27:39.800
I'm Daniel, and I'm an alcoholic.

27:39.880 --> 27:41.735
Hi, Daniel.

27:41.815 --> 27:44.305
I'm gonna be running tonight's meeting,

27:44.385 --> 27:46.440
but before we hear from our speaker,

27:46.520 --> 27:51.211
I'd like to hand out some chips
for various lengths of sobriety.

27:51.291 --> 27:55.082
Now, all of us have had
one day at some point.

27:55.162 --> 27:57.751
And maybe some of us still do.

27:57.831 --> 28:00.402
Are there any newcomers
who'd like to be recognized?

28:03.771 --> 28:05.417
Yeah.

28:08.442 --> 28:11.665
- Chase, alcoholic.
- Hi, Chase.

28:11.745 --> 28:14.602
I have 37 days, so technically,
I'm not a newcomer,

28:14.682 --> 28:17.771
but since we battle
this wily demon one day at a time,

28:17.851 --> 28:20.374
I can't help but feel like
a newcomer every day.

28:20.454 --> 28:23.010
So I wanna share
my experience, strength, and hope.

28:23.090 --> 28:25.661
Anybody with 30 days of sobriety?

28:28.095 --> 28:31.852
I know some of you see me
as a washed-up swashbuckler

28:31.932 --> 28:34.188
who got bored marauding the high seas,

28:34.268 --> 28:37.725
but I've lived all of
my adult life in California.

28:37.805 --> 28:40.394
And as I stand here,

28:40.474 --> 28:42.930
at the start of my campaign,

28:43.010 --> 28:45.299
I wanna let my opponent know that...

28:45.379 --> 28:48.835
"Yo, ho, ho, and the battle's begun."

28:50.184 --> 28:53.358
60 days? Anyone have 60 days?

28:56.657 --> 29:02.082
God grant me the serenity to accept
the things that I cannot change,

29:02.162 --> 29:04.785
the courage to change the things I can,

29:04.865 --> 29:07.471
and the wisdom to know the difference.

29:11.672 --> 29:13.994
- Hey, here you go.
- You gonna give Harper hell, Mr. Mills?

29:14.074 --> 29:16.363
- You bet.
- Oh, man, I love your work.

29:16.443 --> 29:18.265
- Thanks.
- Hey, can I get a selfie with you?

29:18.345 --> 29:20.518
- Yeah, sure.
- Oh, this is great.

29:22.895 --> 29:25.205
- Oh, that's great. Thank you.
- You're welcome.

29:25.285 --> 29:26.840
When can we get outta here?

29:26.920 --> 29:29.810
I feel like we're all gonna be kidnapped
and forced to squeal like pigs.

29:29.890 --> 29:32.212
- Hey, how are ya?
- You have one more speech in Eureka,

29:32.292 --> 29:34.848
then it's San Jose,
San Luis Obispo, and Fresno.

29:34.928 --> 29:37.518
Wait, I thought we were going
back to L.A. before picking back up.

29:37.598 --> 29:39.253
- Hi.
- From here till the election,

29:39.333 --> 29:41.655
- it's pretty much wall-to-wall.
- This is very great.

29:41.735 --> 29:42.690
- Thank you so much.
- Hi.

29:42.770 --> 29:44.591
- Hi.
- Yes, but, uh, Charlie

29:44.671 --> 29:46.160
is getting out of in-patient.

29:46.240 --> 29:49.296
- You knew about these dates, honey.
- Yes, I know.

29:49.376 --> 29:50.597
- Thank you so much.
- Thank you.

29:50.677 --> 29:51.932
- Thank you, I appreciate it.
- Yes.

29:52.012 --> 29:54.635
But I, you know, there's, uh, family group

29:54.715 --> 29:57.938
at the new sober living house,
and I thought we should be there for him.

29:58.018 --> 29:59.807
- Hi.
- Don't do this to me.

29:59.887 --> 30:01.742
- Do what?
- Hi.

30:01.822 --> 30:04.611
If you want, I can arrange
for you to fly back.

30:04.691 --> 30:06.313
- Here you go, sir, you want a burger?
- Yes, please.

30:06.393 --> 30:07.347
There you go.

30:08.527 --> 30:12.019
- Yes?
- Hey, Drake, I'm all packed.

30:12.099 --> 30:15.239
- So anything I need to sign or what?
- Just a minute.

30:18.872 --> 30:21.261
Hey, I wanted to congratulate
you on moving forward

30:21.341 --> 30:23.630
to the next phase of
your Changes Ahead treatment program.

30:23.710 --> 30:25.065
Thank you.

30:25.145 --> 30:27.134
Now, uh, where are those dotted lines, huh?

30:27.214 --> 30:28.802
Hold on, hold on, all right?
We gotta debrief.

30:28.882 --> 30:31.705
- It's part of our discharge procedure.
- Great.

30:31.785 --> 30:33.924
Debrief the shit out of me.

30:35.422 --> 30:38.912
Okay, um, do you have someone responsible

30:38.992 --> 30:42.049
to transport you to
our sober living facility?

30:42.129 --> 30:44.384
- Absolutely.
- # Come on, fuck it #

30:44.464 --> 30:45.419
# Pass the blunt #

30:45.499 --> 30:47.654
# Come on, motherfucker,
said pass the blunt #

30:47.734 --> 30:50.476
- He's very responsible.
- Fine.

30:51.471 --> 30:53.727
If you'll just sign here, and you're all set.

30:53.807 --> 30:55.844
Okey-dokey.

30:57.578 --> 30:59.566
Well, it's been real, Drake.

30:59.646 --> 31:01.401
You, uh, have fun
holding down the fort, okay?

31:01.481 --> 31:03.470
Oh, I will, Charlie,
and unless you're a speed reader,

31:03.550 --> 31:05.973
I'm sure you missed the part
about fraternizing

31:06.053 --> 31:09.676
with people from this facility and how
it applies to when you leave here as well.

31:09.756 --> 31:11.278
- Yeah, shouldn't be a problem.
- Good, good.

31:11.358 --> 31:13.981
But just in case, I went ahead
and let your, uh, sober living house

31:14.061 --> 31:17.217
know about your friendship with Eva.

31:17.297 --> 31:19.486
I let her house know as well.

31:19.566 --> 31:21.555
Friendship during sobriety, not a problem.

31:21.635 --> 31:24.091
Romance, however...

31:24.171 --> 31:26.059
tends to get in the way.

31:26.139 --> 31:30.063
But like you said, that, uh,
shouldn't be a problem, should it?

31:30.143 --> 31:31.965
Yeah, right.

31:32.045 --> 31:33.634
Good luck.

31:35.714 --> 31:39.706
- So, you're finally free. How do you feel?
- Actually, not that shitty.

31:39.786 --> 31:41.842
